name: di-n-butyl sulfoxide

The sulfoxide (S=O) functional group dramatically increases the melting point due to the presence of polar bonding and the ability for the molecule to engage in dipole-dipole interactions. Summing these effects, we have butane's melting point (-138.3) plus four butyl groups (4 * +20), and one sulfoxide group (+80): -138.3 + (4 * 20) + 80.
